title: Ben Youngs warns Australia that England have yet to reveal extent of their attacking potency
text:
Ben Youngs has warned Australia, England’s quarter-final opponents, that Eddie Jones’s side have yet to reveal the full potency of their attacking hand during their World Cup campaign.

Wales’ victory over Uruguay on Sunday confirmed that England will face the Wallabies at Oita Stadium next Saturday, the side that knocked England out of their own World Cup in the final pool match at Twickenham four years ago.

England have since avenged that defeat under Jones, with a streak of six successive victories over the Wallabies since the Australian took over in January 2016.
